pages  ="{31--38}",
isbn   ="ISSN~0252~9742",
abstract="{Conventional algebraic specifications describe data types some times
only implicit with hidden sorts and functions. A more powerful and
elegant technique can be achived by putting more structure into the
specification. Our approach distinguishes between basis sorts and
subsorts. The subsorts, whose carriers are included in the basis sort
