algebra semantics of our specifications, which include declarations
and equations.}"
}

@TECHREPORT{Gogolla:1983:ReportDortmund169,
AUTHOR     ="Martin Gogolla",
TITLE      ="{Algebraic Specifications with Partially Ordered Sorts and Declarations}",
INSTITUTION="{Universit{\"a}t Dortmund, Abteilung Informatik}",
YEAR       ="{1983}",
type       ="{Forschungsbericht}",
number     ="{169}",
abstract="{Conventional algebraic specification techniques cannot express
relationships between sorts formally. The approach presented here puts
more structure into the specification by allowing a partial ordering
on the set of sorts to describe that one sort is a subsort of another
sort. This concept implies that one function can occur more than one
time in the signature with different domains and codomains. Apart from
equations our specifications allow declarations to type a term of a
certain sort to a subsort of the given one. The initial algebra
semantics of our specifications with a partial ordering on the set of
sorts are studied.}"
}

