publisher   ="{IEEE}",
XXXaddress     ="{}",
XXXmonth       ="{}",
XXXnote        ="{}",
abstract  ="{Presenting precisely models and supporting automatic manipulation of
models are at the heart of model-centric software development. A
formal foundation for these tasks is a necessity as well as a
challenge. We present a model-driven approach based on the integration
of two light-weight formal methods, the Object Constraint
Language (OCL) and Triple Graph Grammars (TGGs). OCL together with
