abstract  ="{Within model-driven development, class invariants play a central
role. An essential property of a collection of invariants is the
independence of each single invariant, i.e., the invariant at hand
cannot be deduced from the other invariants. The paper explains with
three example models the details of an approach for automatically
proving and representing invariant independence on the basis of a
